7. name (Inside a Step) - Provides a friendly name for the step.

- name: Print Greeting
Appears in GitHub Actions logs.

8. run - Executes a shell command.

run: echo "Hello"

Multiple commands:
run: |
  pwd
  ls -la
  echo "Done"
  
9. uses - Used to execute a prebuilt GitHub Action.

Example:
- uses: actions/checkout@v4
This action downloads your repository code onto the runner.


Complete Example:
================
name: Hello World

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main

jobs:
  demo:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Print Greeting
        run: echo "Hello World"

      - name: Show Current Directory
        run: pwd

      - name: List Files
        run: ls -la
		

